  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment data to attacker-controlled Cloudflare Worker at install time",
  "details": "The package's dist/setup.js performs a fetch/POST to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev with values read from process.env, sending installer-side environment data to a personal Cloudflare Workers subdomain (wpolanco.workers.dev) that is not associated with any documented vendor identity for this package. Additional bundled files (dist/server.js, dist/crypto.js, dist/store.js) include multiple POST endpoints, base64 decoding patterns feeding into Buffer.from(...,'base64') chains, and a `ping` network primitive — consistent with a remote-controlled agent rather than a benign onboarding tool. The combination of an install/setup-phase outbound POST carrying process.env contents to an unvetted *.workers.dev endpoint constitutes installer data exfiltration to attacker-controlled infrastructure.",
